f:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. IFTTT is best suited for consumers, smart home users, simple automations, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. n8n, meanwhile, shines for developers, self hosters, privacy conscious teams, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2010, IFTTT describes itself as \"Simple conditional automation connecting everyday apps and devices.\" n8n, established in 2019, positions itself as \"Fair-code workflow automation platform with self-hosting option.\" With 9 years between them, IFTTT brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while n8n offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
10:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **n8n** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 6.0), more features (10 vs 7), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean IFTTT is a poor choice — far from it. IFTTT excels in its own right, particularly for consumers and smart home users.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value self-hostable and fair-code licensed, go with n8n. If extremely simple to use matters more to you, IFTTT is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
